"Patrick, Tyler et al continue to produce some of the tastiest stuff around."
"I found it one of those beers that clearly remind you how important serving temperature is. When I first started drinking it, a bit under temperature, I found the vinegar to be overwhelming and found it to be harsh with just a hint of rye. At the proper temperature the acetic, citrus, and rye notes appear balanced."
